rest_of_day_open: I see myself having a low key week, hopefully not too stressful. I have to finish up some work and run some errands. My birthday is coming up within the week so I am getting presents which is nice. I hopefully will make more headway on some side projects I am pursuing.
critical_positive: She was friendly and a good conversation. We didn't go into much depth, but I think overall I was interested in what she had to say. She seemed interested in my life. She also lives in a city that my family member lives in, so we could talk a little about that.
critical_negative: At one point I maybe accidentally brought up politics, even though I didn't mean to. She had asked me a follow-up question and my answer was kind of 'I was worried it would be too conservative here'. But I felt bad about saying that, because she might have been conservative herself.

rest_of_day_open: I hope that the rest of the week is cooler and that I'll be able to get more sleep. The heat wave and resulting insomnia has been really hard. I'm looking forward to a conversation with my coach and maybe visiting my mom. I'd like to make a bit more money on Prolific.
critical_positive: We were both generally friendly and cooperative. I think that people who come to have these conversations are generally prepared to have a talk with a stranger and cooperate in making it happen. We found things to chat about, although many of the subjects were fairly trivial. Amanda seemed nice.
critical_negative: We didn't really have that much in common and the conversation lacked a certain level of energy. While it wasn't a strain, I'm not sure we'd have talked for this long if we didn't have a 25 minute chat requirement. Many of the subjects we talked about were pretty trivial.
